&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Commercial Lead — Kapacity.io, part of EnergyHub&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location : Nordics or Western Europe - Remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Kapacity.io helps energy retailers unlock residential energy flexibility — making residential households active participants in a cleaner, more resilient power grid. Kapacity.io is EnergyHub&#39;s European expansion arm, with strong traction and a mandate to grow fast. This role exists to build the go to market strategy: develop the market, open the right doors, and create the motion that drives our next phase of growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the commercial motion. Create the process, structure, and repeatability success is built on — qualification frameworks, proposals, positioning, pricing input. The team will learn from how you work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the market. Identify and engage the right people at energy retailers across the Nordics, Germany, France, Benelux and the UK. Use the network you have, build the one you don&#39;t, and keep qualified opportunities moving forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the room. Lead executive-level conversations with senior buyer and technical audiences — in person, remote, and at industry conferences. Monthly travel is expected, both for events and customer visits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape commercial strategy. You&#39;ll have direct input into how we go to market, not just execute on it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feed intelligence back. Stay close to policy, regulation, and competitor moves in your markets. What you hear shapes product and leadership decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect actively through conferences, direct outreach, and network development to find and engage the right people in energy retail and flexibility roles across Europe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;In year one, you&#39;ve established a genuine presence in our priority markets — meaningful relationships with the right people at energy retailers, a healthy and honest pipeline, and a commercial process the team can build on. You&#39;re not inheriting someone else&#39;s work; you&#39;re creating the foundation.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record in commercial roles — business development, sales, or strategic accounts — in B2B or enterprise environments. You&#39;ve built pipeline, not just worked one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience selling SaaS or technology into regulated or complex buying environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who can build a sales process, not just run one. Self-sufficient on proposals and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuinely social — you build trust quickly with senior stakeholders and thrive at conferences and industry events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clear, confident communicator across technical and commercial audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable operating without structure and creating it where it doesn&#39;t exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English required. German, French, or Swedish is a meaningful advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with energy markets, demand flexibility, or distributed energy resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An existing network among energy retailers in the Nordics, Germany, or the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience contributing to pricing, packaging, or market position

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Opportunity: Marketing Writer, Energy Sector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced Marketing Writer to help articulate how EnergyHub is transforming the energy industry. This role is focused on writing and editing high‑quality marketing content that supports brand and content marketing initiatives across multiple B2B and B2C channels. You’ll partner closely with marketing, product, clients, and subject‑matter experts to execute clear, compelling written content for technical and non‑technical audiences — from utility engineers to energy customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is an execution‑focused role for a strong writer with deep experience with the energy sector.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope of Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing content creation: &lt;/strong&gt;Write and edit blog posts, long-form articles, whitepapers, reports, email campaigns, social media copy, and thought leadership content focused on the energy industry and EnergyHub’s solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event and industry content support: &lt;/strong&gt;Contribute written content related to industry events, conferences, awards, and campaigns as needed (e.g., presentation support, event promo campaigns, or follow‑up materials).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Website and product messaging:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop clear, accurate copy for solution pages, product overviews, landing pages, and other web content that explains complex energy concepts with precision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer and sales enablement materials:&lt;/strong&gt; Author case studies, one‑pagers, presentations, and customer‑facing collateral that support go‑to‑market efforts and sales conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing and editing marketing or technical content within the energy industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A knack for storytelling and a portfolio that shows your ability to explain complex ideas clearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A natural curiosity and eagerness to explore complex technical topics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort using AI tools for brainstorming, drafting, and editing to meet quality and accuracy standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working as part of an ongoing, embedded marketing team, contributing to shared goals and timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in English, Communications, Journalism, Engineering, or a related technical field preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About EnergyHub&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EnergyHub empowers utilities and their customers to create a clean, distributed energy future. We help consumers turn their smart thermostats, EVs, batteries, and other products into virtual power plants that keep the grid stable and enable higher penetration of solar and wind power&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EnergyHub is an Equal Opportunity Employer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EOE, Including Disability/Vets. Reasonable accommodations are available for individuals with disabilities throughout the application process. If you are a person with a disability needing assistance with the application process, please contact accommodations.apply@energyhub.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In connection with your application, we collect information that identifies, reasonably relates to or describes you (“Personal Information”). The categories of Personal Information that we may collect include your name, government-issued identification number(s), email address, mailing address, other contact information, emergency contact information, employment history, educational history, and demographic information.&amp;nbsp; We

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our Controller, you’ll partner closely with our executive team to help build the systems and processes that strengthen the G&amp;amp;A backbone of the company. As an independent subsidiary business of Alarm.com, we have been a part of a public company reporting environment for the past decade, though have been largely operating with a centralized G&amp;amp;A function at the Alarm.com level. We’re taking a meaningful step towards a decentralized model at this stage in our maturity and hiring a Controller to report directly to our CEO, with a dotted line to the Alarm.com CFO. The role will blend traditional corporate controllership responsibilities with divisional ones, relying upon and coordinating with Alarm.com finance leaders in areas such as Technical Accounting, Tax, Internal Audit, FP&amp;amp;A, and Investor Relations. This is an opportunity to be on the ground floor of a dedicated finance and accounting movement for a scaling SaaS business within a public company environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accounting Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Drive an efficient and accurate monthly close process and quarterly financial reporting cadence, including identifying opportunities to accelerate close calendars, improve automation, and streamline processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Establish and maintain robust internal controls to safeguard company assets and ensure accurate financial records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Lead, mentor, and develop the accounting and collections team to strengthen technical skills and business acumen, fostering a culture of urgency, excellence, and problem solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Collaborate with the Technical Accounting &amp;amp; SEC Reporting team at Alarm.com to ensure GAAP-compliant financial records and reporting of complex accounting matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Collaborate with the commercial teams (Sales, Client Success, Client Operations, Partner Solutions) to ensure billing and accounting processes are well-defined and communicated and that all teams are aligned to supporting accounting and billing operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Transformation &amp;amp; Business Partnership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Partner with the Alarm.com Finance Transformation team and IT resources to evaluate, enhance, and automate accounting and billing systems and processes, driving operational efficiency and scalability. Alarm.com will be launching an ERP implementation imminently, and you will be on the frontline on behalf of EnergyHub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Build and nurture trusted partnerships with business leaders, demonstrating the accounting function’s strategic value and alignment with broader company goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Navigate the complex balance between customer centricity and a growth culture with stewardship of the P&amp;amp;L and public company reporting requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other duties as assigned.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· 12+ years of progressive accounting experience, preferably within technology-focused corporate environments and/or public accounting, including exposure to both early-stage and public companies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Active CPA required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Extensive experience with multiple ERP systems and participation in ERP implementation projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Proven track record implementing ERP-adjacent systems (e.g. cloud billing systems) to streamline workflows and increase efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Demonstrated ability to build accounting functions capable of supporting scale and complexity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Strong command of GAAP, technical accounting, and financial reporting standards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Unflappable under pressure: you stay calm, clear-headed, and focused when the stakes are high&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Curious, proactive,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Executive Assistant, you’ll work at the heart of our leadership team and play a critical role in making sure the business runs smoothly at the highest levels. This is not a traditional administrative role - you’ll be a strategic partner and trusted operator, owning key workflows, ensuring airtight execution, and keeping things moving in a fast-paced environment. If you thrive on high ownership, thoughtful execution, and supporting bold leaders, we want to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is key to our company’s day-to-day operations, and so it is required to work from our Brooklyn office 4-5 days per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Executive Assistance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a right-hand partner to the CEO, acting as an extension of their time, energy, and judgment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex scheduling and calendar coordination across time zones with precision and thoughtfulness for three executives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare for high-stakes meetings: create agendas, materials, briefs, and follow-ups to ensure top-tier execution and communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate internal communications and support executive alignment across functions and teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle sensitive information with discretion and professionalism; maintain absolute confidentiality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate travel logistics and day-to-day operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and refine scalable administrative processes that keep our executive function running like a well-oiled machine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationships with vendors, service providers, and landlord, ensuring that all items are invoiced and paid on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the company’s corporate credit card ensuring invoices are submitted and paid on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate weekly EnergyGrub for the Brooklyn office, taking into consideration dietary restrictions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General physical office duties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A seasoned operator with 8+ years of experience in executive support, business operations, or a similar function; tech, startup, or fast-paced environments are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unflappable under pressure: you stay calm, clear-headed, and focused when the stakes are high&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curious, proactive, and solution-oriented: you’re always two steps ahead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and detail-oriented: nothing slips through the cracks on your watch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An exceptional communicator with strong emotional intelligence and sound judgment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that sponsorship of new applicants for employment authorization, or any other immigration-related support, is not available for this position at this time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work for EnergyHub?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate with outstanding people:&lt;/strong&gt; Our employees work hard, do great work, and enjoy collaborating and learning from each other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Make an immediate impact:&lt;/strong&gt; New employees can expect to be given real responsibility for bringing new technologies to the marketplace. You are empowered to perform as soon as you join the team!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gain well rounded experience:&lt;/strong&gt; EnergyHub offers a diverse and dynamic environment where you will get the chance to work directly with executives and develop expertise across multiple areas of the business.&lt;/li&gt;
